Bus Tickets
Paytm is only a bus ticket agent. It does not operate buses or offers bus transport services. In order to provide a comprehensive choice of bus operators, departure times and prices to customers, Paytm has tied up with many bus operators and service providers.
Paytm’s advice to customers is to choose the bus operators who they are aware of and whose service they are comfortable with.
Paytm’s responsibilities include:
issuing a valid ticket (a ticket that will be accepted by the bus operator) for its network of bus operators;
providing refund and support in the event of cancellation; and
providing customer support and information in case of any delays/inconvenience.
Paytm’s responsibilities do not include:
The bus operator’s bus not departing/reaching on time;
The bus operator’s employees being unprofessional or engaging in unlawful conduct;
The bus operator’s bus seats, etc., not being up to the customer’s expectation;
The bus operator cancelling the trip due to any reason;
The baggage of the customer getting lost/stolen/damaged;
The bus operator changing a customer’s seat at the last minute to accommodate any of the following passengers: senior citizens, children, pregnant women, persons with disability or any other person in a situation of emergency;
The customer waiting at the wrong boarding point (please call the bus operator to find out the exact boarding point if You are not a regular traveller on that particular bus or route);
The bus operator changing the boarding point and/or using a pick-up vehicle at the boarding point to take customers to the bus departure point.
The arrival and departure times mentioned on the ticket are only tentative timings. However, the bus will not leave the source before the time that is mentioned on the ticket.
Passengers are required to furnish the following at the time of boarding the bus:
A copy of the ticket (a printout of the ticket or the printout of the ticket e mail).
Identity proof (Aadhaar Card, Driving license, Student ID card, Company ID card, Passport, PAN card or Voter ID card). Failing to do so, they may not be allowed to board the bus.
Passengers must also be aware of the following :
Change of bus: In case the bus operator changes the type of bus due to some reason, Paytm will refund the differential amount to the customer upon being intimated by the customers within 24 hours of the journey.
Cancellation Policy: Passengers are expected to read the ticket cancellation policy carefully. Tickets will be cancelled as per the cancellation policy linked with the ticket. The transaction charges will not be refunded in the event of ticket cancellation.
Refund policy mentioned on the ticket is indicative. The actual cancellation charges are determined by bus operators and bus providers at the actual time of cancellation. Paytm has no role in governing the cancellation charges.
Cancellation charges are calculated on the actual fare of the ticket. If any discount coupons are used while purchasing the ticket, the discounted value would be used to calculate the refund amount when a ticket is cancelled.
In case a booking confirmation e mail and SMS gets delayed or fails because of technical reasons or as a result of incorrect e mail ID/phone number provided by the user, etc., a ticket will be considered ‘booked’ as long as the ticket shows up on the confirmation page of the Paytm Platform.
Amenities on the buses as shown on Paytm have been configured and provided by the bus service provider (bus operator). These amenities will be provided unless there are some exceptions on certain days. Please note that Paytm provides this information in good faith to help passengers to make an informed decision. Provision of video, air conditioning and any such other services mentioned by Paytm’s travel partners in the buses is their own responsibility. Any refunds/claims due to non-functioning or un-availability of these services needs to be settled directly with the bus service provider.
Paytm is not responsible for any kind of journey inconvenience, injury or death, caused during the journey or flowing from the journey.
For any issues relating to cancellation or refund, the passenger may contact Paytm within 15 days of date of travel, beyond which period request would not be processed.
Paytm may call the mobile phone number provided by You while registering with the Paytm Platform, or any updated mobile number subsequently provided by You on the Paytm Platform, or contact You via e-mail, for the purpose of collecting feedback from You regarding Your travel bookings, including but not limited to the bus facilities and/or services of the bus operator.
Grievances and claims related to the bus journey should be reported to Paytm support team within 10 days of Your travel date.
Refunds in cases where Airline is declared as Insolvent or Bankrupt
Paytm shall not be liable to pay any refunds whatsoever in cases where the airline closes its operations or declares itself as insolvent or has been declared as insolvent in any legal proceedings. The customers or clients or agents shall not hold Paytm liable to pay the refunds as assured at the time of booking of ticket in cases where the airline closes its operation or declares itself as insolvent or has been declared as insolvent in any legal proceedings.
Movie Tickets
Movie Ticketing Policy
This movie ticketing policy shall apply in respect of the sale and purchase of movie tickets made by a customer/You, on the Paytm Platform.
Paytm is an intermediary within the meaning of the Information Technology Act, 2000 and the rules thereunder and merely facilitates, on behalf of Orbgen Technologies Private Limited (“Orbgen”) (and which is operating under the brand name “Ticketnew”), the sale and purchase of movie tickets between the merchant and customer / You, which has been powered by Orbgen. For the purposes of this policy, a “merchant” shall mean a cinema owner/cinema partner or the person owning inventory of movie tickets that are available for sale on the Paytm Platform. Paytm does not, at any point of time during any transaction between the customer / You and the merchant, either take the ownership of any products or services offered by the merchant or receives any payment made by the customer / You for the booking of tickets on the Paytm Platform. Further, Paytm does not, at any point, assert any rights or claims over the products / services offered by the merchant to the customer / You.
In using the Paytm Platform for purchasing movie tickets, customer / You explicitly agree to the following terms (as may be applicable):
Bookings on the Paytm Platform are facilitated solely on behalf of Orbgen.
Bookings for the tickets once made by customer / You cannot be cancelled, modified, exchanged or refunded unless such policies are provided at the cinema / Paytm Platform and opted-in by the customer / You while booking the movie tickets.
Your booking confirmation will be sent via an e-mail and / or SMS to the Paytm registered contact details and/or shown in the movies section of the Paytm Platform.
Booking ID and / or order ID generated through the Paytm Platform, which also includes the Paytm website/application shall be considered as a valid booking ID by Paytm. Any claims / issues pertaining to the booking ID should be raised with and resolved at Paytm’s customer care and the decision of Paytm shall be final and binding. Such complaints shall be raised on the Paytm Platform via Help & Support section.
Customer / You are advised to keep Your booking IDs secure and in the possession of either Yourself or an authorized representative. Please be aware that anyone who possesses the booking ID will be permitted to exchange it for a valid ticket, without further security checks, as long as they are considered to be the authorized holder of the booking ID.
Customer / You, or the person collecting the ticket(s) on your behalf, will need to present the booking ID / QR code at the counter in order to avail a physical ticket / digital ticket from the cinema box office at the premises of the concerned cinema hall.
Please add movietickets@paytm.com, no-reply@paytm.com, support@ticketnew.com, no-reply@ticketnew.com and noreply@ticketnew.com to Your address book to ensure e-mail delivery in your Paytm registered e-mail ID’s inbox / spambox. Paytm and Orbgen shall not be responsible for any loss caused due to the confirmation e-mail or any other e-mail relating to the ticket booking process not being delivered to Your primary e-mail inbox. You may also refer to the booking confirmation screen to check the booking details.
If You do not receive the booking ID (in the form of SMS / e mail / in-app notification / on the Paytm Platform screen) after submitting payment information, or if You receive an error message or service interruption after submitting payment information, You should refresh the page / relaunch the Paytm Platform to get the updated status as booking confirmation can take up to 30 (thirty) minutes. If no booking ID is received even after 30 (thirty) minutes of payment, you should immediately report to the Paytm customer care. Paytm and/or Orbgen and/or shall not be responsible for any losses occurred during this process, due to any default on the part of banks, payment aggregators etc. or for reasons not attributable to Paytm and/or Orbgen.
Booking charges and / or the internet handling charges are levied on all tickets booked online on the Paytm Platform.
The holder of a physical ticket / digital ticket is deemed to be the owner of the ticket(s).
In some cases, cinemas / theatre might request the customer / You to show the movie booking confirmation e-mail / SMS / printout / confirmation message of the movie booking on the Paytm Platform in order to validate Your booking. As per the cinema / theatre admission policy, in case a physical ticket is lost or misplaced or digital ticket is not presented via the Paytm Platform, a duplicate ticket might not be issued. Final decision to allow entry will be at the sole discretion of the cinema / theatre management.
Before purchasing the tickets, You are advised to check the warning about age restrictions for that particular movie. As per applicable laws, individuals under the age of 18 (eighteen) shall not be permitted to enter the cinema / theatre for movies with an A (adult) rating. Additionally, You are further advised to check for any other applicable entry restrictions or ratings that may be in place for specific movies.
3D charges (wherever applicable) may already be included in the ticket prices or may be charged separately from ticket prices or may be collected by the cinema / theatre partner on the cinema premises. Details of charges collected by Paytm will be shown before making the payment for the ticket(s). Customer / You should review the transaction amount before making the booking.
As per the cinema / theatre admission policy, You need to purchase tickets for children above the age of 3 (three) years.
As per the cinema / theatre admission policy, outside food and beverages are not allowed inside the cinema hall’s premises.
You are advised to avoid carrying laptops, handycams, digital cameras and any such electronic equipment to the cinema / theatre. You are advised to check with the cinema / theatre about any restrictions which might be in place for that particular cinema / theatre.
If the merchant cancels or reschedules the movie / show, Paytm and/or Orbgen shall not be held responsible for such cancellation(s) or reschedule. In the event that a merchant cancels or reschedules a movie, Paytm will notify customer / You on best effort basis and shall provide a refund according to the cinema / theatre's policy. Where refund is permissible as per the cinema / theatre's policy, Paytm shall automatically issue a refund to Your original payment mode(s) / other payment mode as opted by customer / You with applicable deductions from the amount paid by customer / You for the movie ticket(s) (including any add-on products) booked on Paytm. After Paytm processes the refund, the amount shall be reflected in your bank account / payment mode as per bank timelines.
If You pay an incorrect amount for a movie ticket, whether due to an error in the displayed price on the Paytm Platform or otherwise communicated to customer / You, or if You are able to book a movie ticket before its scheduled on-sale or presale date, or if You book a movie ticket that was not supposed to have been released for sale, Paytm reserves the right to cancel that particular movie ticket or order and refund the amount that You had paid to the original payment mode(s). This  policy applies even in the case of human error or a transactional malfunction on the Paytm Platform.
All seat layouts are only for representational purposes and the distance between rows including distance from the movie screen can differ from the actual cinema / theatre.
In some cases either the entire cinema / theatre or a few seating categories of the cinema / theatre could be free seating. In free seating cinema / theatre  seating categories, customer / You can only select the count of seats to be booked. No particular seat is booked and booking details will only show the count of seats booked. In such cases, seats are allotted on a First come First Serve basis by the cinema / theatre partner.
Some cinemas / theatres allow customers to book movie tickets on Paytm Platform by only paying the booking charges / internet handling charges. Ticket price amount is collected by the cinema / theatre partner at the cinema / theatre itself before allowing entry to the cinema / theatre. Information about cinemas / theatres working on such a model will be shown to the customer / You during the movie booking flow. Customer / You should check the details shown before proceeding with such booking.
All images shown in the food & beverages section are for representational purposes only.
In the food & beverages section, any nutritional and / or energy and / or allergens information provided against an item is an approximation and is basis the information shared per-serving by the cinema and is displayed “as-is”. It may differ / vary based on ingredients & portion sizes.
By booking a ticket on the Paytm Platform, customer / You agree and undertake to adhere to and comply with the terms and conditions of respective cinemas / theatres in respect of all the bookings made by customer / You through the Paytm Platform.
We may share booking information with Orbgen and the merchants, such as customer / Your name, booking ID, customer’s phone number and / or e-mail ID including any other relevant information for smooth customer entry flow within the cinema / theatre premises and such information would be used for smooth booking experience and / or availing loyalty or rewards points benefits from the cinema/theatre partners, if any and the customer/ You provide your explicit consent for us to share customer / Your data with any third parties as may be required. The customer/ You also agree and acknowledge that the third parties with whom customer / Your data is shared shall be classified as the owner of such transferred data and shall have the ability to deal with and/or process such data in any manner that they deem fit.
By accepting the T&Cs, including the specific terms and conditions in this section, customer / You accept that Paytm and/or Orbgen may send alerts to the mobile phone number / e-mail / Paytm Platform notification / WhatsApp as per the details provided by the customer / You while registering on the Paytm Platform or to any such number replaced and informed by the customer / You subsequently.
Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, neither Paytm and Orbgen nor their respective affiliates or their respective officers, directors, employees, agents shall have any liability to the customer / You or to any third party for any indirect, incidental, special or consequential damages or any loss of revenue or profits arising under or relating to the T&Cs, the Paytm Platform or Paytm Services, even if any of the said parties had been advised of, knew of, or should have known of, the possibility of such damages. Paytm’s and Orbgen’s  (and their respective  affiliates, officers, directors, employees, and agents) combined maximum aggregate liability to the customer / You for any causes whatsoever, and regardless of the form of action (whether liability arises due to negligence or any other tort, breach of contract, violation of statute, misrepresentation or for any other reason), shall at all times be limited to the ticket price or Rs. 5,000, whichever is lower. To the maximum extent permitted by law, the customer / You waive, release, discharge and hold harmless Paytm and Orbgen, and their respective affiliates and each of their directors, officers, employees, and agents, from any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, expenses and causes of action arising out of customer / Your use of the Paytm Platform and/or Paytm services. In case of any issues, the interpretation of the same shall be at the sole discretion of Paytm and shall be considered as final and binding on customer / You.
Under no circumstances should customer / You entertain anyone who is selling printouts or SMS messages of booking IDs claiming to be generated by Paytm. If customer / You happen to come across someone who is engaged in this activity, it is important that you report it promptly to Paytm customer care team and to customer / Your local police station.
Cinema Cancellation Policy
1. Cinema / theatre partners may choose to provide flexibility of movie ticket cancellation at their own discretion. These details as made available to Paytm will be available to customer / You at the time of the movie ticket booking.
2. Benefits of cinema / theatre partner’s cancellation policy would be passed on to customer / You on “as-is” basis and Paytm/ Orbgen has no rights / control on the cancellation policy of cinema/ theatre partners.
3. Cinema / theatre partners may change the refund slab of ticket cancellation without any prior information and the refund amount may vary from time-to-time. Customer / You should check the complete booking and cancellation policy before proceeding to book movie tickets on the Paytm Platform.
4. Cancellation charges provided by cinema/theatre partners will be applicable on cancellation of any booking which may vary from time to time or based on customer / Your booking and cinema / theatre cancellation policy. Paytm and/or Orbgen shall not be held responsible for any such changes made to booking and / or cancellation policy.
5. Cinema / theatre partners may choose to provide such cancellation policy benefits to all or some selective users at their sole discretion.
6. Partial cancellation of an order / booking / ticket(s) is not allowed.
7. Benefits of any applied promocode on the order / booking will be considered as redeemed / fulfilled if the ticket(s) are cancelled by customer / You and the benefits of the promocode shall not be availed on any other order / booking.
8. Refund received for the cancelled booking (if any) will be after deduction of any cancellation charges, booking charges, internet handling charges, food vouchers, 3D glass charges, applicable taxes and promotional benefits.
9. If the cancellation of the booking is unsuccessful for any reason, a refund will not be issued and the booking will be considered 'not cancelled' i.e. valid. Customer / You may try to cancel the booking after some time if the booking is still under the cancellation window as per the cancellation policy. In such cases customer / You must contact the Paytm customer care team and / or cinema / theatre customer support with customer / Your booking details.
10. Paytm has the right, in its sole discretion, at anytime to adjust, supplement, modify, revise, terminate, or carry out any necessary alterations to this policy and/or the cancellation feature, either entirely or partially.
Food vouchers policy (if applicable)
1. Paytm may offer food vouchers by partnering with cinema chains to offer you food vouchers which can be redeemed at the cinema / theatre premises.
2. The food vouchers may be available for purchase in the ‘food section’ of the Paytm Platform while booking movie tickets for the respective cinemas / theatres.
3. On buying the food voucher (if available), customer/You will get a code through email and / or SMS which customer / You can use to purchase food and beverage items at the cinema / theatre premises. Customer / You can also find the code on the order summary page which can be accessed by selecting ‘Your order’ in your ‘order history’ of customer / Your Paytm website / application.
4. Based on the respective cinema partners’ discretion, food vouchers purchased from any national / regional cinema chains may be valid at most of the cinemas under that cinema chain with few exceptions. Customer / You are advised to check the details / terms & conditions of the food voucher before making the purchase.
5. Each food voucher may have an expiry date attached to it and is valid for any show till the expiry of that food voucher.
6. The food voucher is non-refundable, either before or after the expiry or in case of movie / show cancellation or cancellation of booking as per cinema / theatre movie ticket cancellation policy.
7. Partial redemption of the food voucher is not allowed.
8. Cinema / theatre partner may allow only one food voucher to be redeemed in one transaction and any excess amount in addition to the one mentioned on the food voucher needs to be paid at the cinema / theatre.
